README for modblock

 Kernel Module Blocker for Unix-like systems (Now Debian Only)
  You can use this script to block any kernel module.
  It -Simply- add it to the blacklist, And removes it when you "allow" it.

Installation:
	 sudo ./modblock -i
Usage:
	Block:
	 sudo modblock -b mod1 mod2 .. modN
	Unblock(Allow):
         sudo modblock -a mod1 mod2 .. modN
         Mixed Input:
	  sudo modblock -b mod1 mod2 .. modN -a mod1 mod2 .. modN
	  #You can block and allow any number of modules in one line
	  sudo modblock -b mod1 mod2 -a mod3 -b mod4 -b mod5 #Valid
	List:
	 sudo modblock -l  #to list all
	 sudo modblock -ll #to list all but one per line
	Help:
	 sudo modblock

Thanks to Mohamed Mohsen (linuxer9) for suggestions

